[{"location":"guide/#User-Guide","page":"User Guide","title":"User Guide","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Usage-Examples","page":"User Guide","title":"Usage Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Basic-Usage-(No-Deployment)","page":"User Guide","title":"Basic Usage (No Deployment)","text":"For local documentation only:\n\nusing PkgTemplates\nusing PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin\n\nt = Template(;\n    user=\"YourUsername\",\n    plugins=[DocumenterShiki()]  # Defaults to NoDeploy\n)\n\nt(\"MyPackage\")","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Configuration-Options","page":"User Guide","title":"Configuration Options","text":"The DocumenterShiki constructor accepts the following options:\n\ntheme::String: Light theme (default: \"github-light\")\ndark_theme::String: Dark theme (default: \"github-dark\")\nlanguages::Vector{String}: Programming languages to support (default: [\"julia\", \"javascript\", \"python\", \"bash\", \"json\", \"yaml\", \"toml\"])\ncdn_url::String: CDN URL for Shiki (default: \"https://esm.sh\")\nassets::Vector{String}: Additional asset files to copy\nlogo::Logo: Documentation logo (light and dark variants)\nmakedocs_kwargs::Dict{Symbol,Any}: Additional arguments for makedocs()\ndevbranch::String: Development branch name\nedit_link::Union{String,Symbol}: Edit link type\n\nSee available Shiki themes for theme options.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Deployment-Types","page":"User Guide","title":"Deployment Types","text":"DocumenterShiki supports the same deployment types as the standard Documenter plugin:\n\nDocumenterShiki() or DocumenterShiki{NoDeploy}(): Local documentation only âœ… Tested\nDocumenterShiki{GitHubActions}(): Deploy to GitHub Pages via GitHub Actions Supported\nDocumenterShiki{TravisCI}(): Deploy to GitHub Pages via Travis CI Supported\nDocumenterShiki{GitLabCI}(): Deploy to GitLab Pages via GitLab CI Supported\n\nNote: When using deployment types other than NoDeploy, you must include the corresponding CI plugin in your template.\n\nExample (NoDeploy - tested):\n\nusing PkgTemplates\nusing PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin\n\nt = Template(;\n    user=\"YourUsername\",\n    plugins=[DocumenterShiki()]\n)\nt(\"MyPackage\")","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Comparison-with-Standard-Documenter","page":"User Guide","title":"Comparison with Standard Documenter","text":"Feature Documenter DocumenterShiki\nSyntax Highlighting highlight.js Shiki (VS Code engine)\nTheme Quality Basic Professional, consistent\nTheme Customization Limited 100+ themes available\nLanguage Support Good Excellent (240+ languages)\nDark Mode Manual Automatic switching\nSetup Complexity Low Low (automatic)\nBuild Speed Fast Fast (CDN-based)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Requirements","page":"User Guide","title":"Requirements","text":"Julia 1.8 or later\nPkgTemplates 0.7 or later\nNode.js 18+ (for building documentation)\npnpm or npm (for Shiki dependencies)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Generated-Package-Structure","page":"User Guide","title":"Generated Package Structure","text":"When you generate a package with DocumenterShiki, it creates:\n\nMyPackage/\nâ”œâ”€â”€ docs/\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ make.jl              # Documentation build script\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ShikiHighlighter.jl  # Shiki integration module\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ src/\nâ”‚       â””â”€â”€ index.md         # Documentation homepage\nâ”œâ”€â”€ package.json             # Node.js dependencies\nâ”œâ”€â”€ build-shiki.js          # Shiki build script\nâ””â”€â”€ ...","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Building-Documentation","page":"User Guide","title":"Building Documentation","text":"In the generated package:\n\n# Install Node.js dependencies\npnpm install\n\n# Build documentation\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Live-Examples","page":"User Guide","title":"Live Examples","text":"To see Shiki syntax highlighting in action with various themes and languages, visit the DocumenterShikiDemo showcase.\n\nThe demo includes:\n\nInteractive theme switching\nCopy-to-clipboard functionality\nReal-world code examples\n\nThis demo site was itself generated using PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin! See GENERATION.md for the exact template command used to generate the package skeleton.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Exported-Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Exported Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Index","page":"API Reference","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin.DocumenterShiki","page":"API Reference","title":"PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin.DocumenterShiki","text":"DocumenterShiki{T}(;\n    theme=\"github-light\",\n    dark_theme=\"github-dark\",\n    languages=[\"julia\", \"javascript\", \"python\", \"bash\", \"json\", \"yaml\", \"toml\"],\n    cdn_url=\"https://esm.sh\",\n    assets=String[],\n    logo=Logo(),\n    makedocs_kwargs=Dict{Symbol,Any}(),\n    canonical_url=make_canonical(T),\n    devbranch=nothing,\n    edit_link=:commit,\n    make_jl=default_file(\"documenter_shiki\", \"make.jlt\"),\n    index_md=default_file(\"documenter_shiki\", \"index.md\"),\n    shiki_highlighter_jl=default_file(\"documenter_shiki\", \"ShikiHighlighter.jlt\"),\n)\n\nPkgTemplates plugin for generating package templates with DocumenterShiki.\n\nDocumentation deployment depends on T, where T is some supported CI plugin, or NoDeploy to only support local documentation builds.\n\nSupported Type Parameters\n\nGitHubActions: Deploys documentation to GitHub Pages with GitHubActions\nTravisCI: Deploys documentation to GitHub Pages with TravisCI\nGitLabCI: Deploys documentation to GitLab Pages with GitLabCI\nNoDeploy (default): Does not set up documentation deployment\n\nKeyword Arguments (Shiki-specific)\n\ntheme::String: Light mode theme (default: \"github-light\")\ndark_theme::String: Dark mode theme (default: \"github-dark\")\nlanguages::Vector{String}: Supported languages (default: julia, javascript, python, bash, json, yaml, toml)\ncdn_url::String: CDN URL for Shiki (default: \"https://esm.sh\")\n\nKeyword Arguments (Documenter-inherited)\n\nassets::Vector{String}: Additional asset files\nlogo::Logo: Logo configuration\nmakedocs_kwargs::Dict{Symbol, Any}: Additional makedocs() arguments\ncanonical_url::Union{Function, Nothing}: Canonical URL function or string\ndevbranch::Union{String, Nothing}: Development branch name\nedit_link::Union{String, Symbol, Nothing}: Edit link configuration\n\nTemplate Files\n\nmake_jl::String: Path to make.jl template\nindex_md::String: Path to index.md template\nshiki_highlighter_jl::String: Path to ShikiHighlighter.jl template\n\nExamples\n\n# Local documentation only\nDocumenterShiki()\n\n# With GitHub Actions deployment\nDocumenterShiki{GitHubActions}(\n    theme=\"github-light\",\n    dark_theme=\"github-dark\"\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin.Logo","page":"API Reference","title":"PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin.Logo","text":"Logo(; light=nothing, dark=nothing)\n\nLogo configuration for documentation.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nlight::Union{String, Nothing}: Path to a logo file for the light (default) theme.\ndark::Union{String, Nothing}: Path to a logo file for the dark theme.\n\nSource: https://github.com/JuliaCI/PkgTemplates.jl/blob/v0.7.56/src/plugins/documenter.jl#L9-L21\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin.jl","page":"Home","title":"PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin.jl","text":"A PkgTemplates plugin for DocumenterShiki - bringing modern Shiki syntax highlighting to Julia package documentation","category":"section"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Home","title":"Overview","text":"PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin is the first standalone third-party plugin for PkgTemplates.jl. It extends PkgTemplates with support for DocumenterShiki, enabling VS Code-quality syntax highlighting powered by Shiki in your package documentation.\n\nWhen you generate a new Julia package with this plugin, it automatically sets up DocumenterShiki with:\n\nModern Shiki syntax highlighting\nLight/dark theme support\nConfigurable color themes and languages\nCI/CD integration (GitHub Actions, Travis CI, GitLab CI)\nAll necessary template files and Node.js dependencies","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","title":"Quick Start","text":"using PkgTemplates\nusing PkgTemplatesShikiPlugin\n\n# Create a template with DocumenterShiki\nt = Template(;\n    user=\"YourGitHubUsername\",\n    plugins=[\n        Git(),\n        GitHubActions(),\n        DocumenterShiki{GitHubActions}(\n            theme=\"github-light\",\n            dark_theme=\"github-dark\"\n        ),\n    ]\n)\n\n# Generate a new package\nt(\"MyAwesomePackage\")\n\nThis creates a new Julia package with DocumenterShiki documentation pre-configured and ready to build.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"ðŸŽ¨ Modern Syntax Highlighting: VS Code-quality highlighting powered by Shiki\nðŸŒ“ Theme Support: Built-in light/dark theme switching\nðŸ“¦ Automatic Setup: All documentation files and dependencies configured automatically\nðŸ”§ Highly Configurable: Customize themes, languages, and Documenter options\nâš¡ CDN-based: No bundling required, loads Shiki from CDN\nðŸš€ CI/CD Ready: Works with GitHub Actions, Travis CI, and GitLab CI\nâœ… Well Tested: Comprehensive test suite (45 tests)","category":"section"}]
